The paper presents a machine learning approach to predict the quality of a user's experience on a telco network in real-time. This involves capturing and analyzing large amounts of data, which falls under the category of big data and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper also deals with telecommunications networks, customer transactions, and customer service.
